  91     def _register_finder(self, finder_name, finder):
  92         # type: (str, Union[WindowsFinder, PythonFinder]) -> "SystemPath"
  93         if finder_name not in self.__finders:
  94             self.__finders[finder_name] = finder

  97     def clear_caches(self):
  98         for key in ["executables", "python_executables", "version_dict", "path_entries"]:
  99             if key in self.__dict__:
 100                 del self.__dict__[key]
 101         for finder in list(self.__finders.keys()):
 102             del self.__finders[finder]
 103         self.__finders = {}
 104         return attr.evolve(
 105             self,
 106             executables=[],
 107             python_executables={},
 108             python_version_dict=defaultdict(list),
 109             version_dict=defaultdict(list),
 110             pyenv_finder=None,
 111             windows_finder=None,
 112             asdf_finder=None,
 113             path_order=[],
 114             paths=defaultdict(PathEntry),
 115         )

 117     def __del__(self):
 118         for key in ["executables", "python_executables", "version_dict", "path_entries"]:
 119             try:
 120                 del self.__dict__[key]
 121             except KeyError:
 122                 pass
 123         for finder in list(self.__finders.keys()):
 124             del self.__finders[finder]
 125         self.__finders = {}
 126         self._python_executables = {}
 127         self._executables = []
 128         self.python_version_dict = defaultdict(list)
 129         self._version_dict = defaultdict(list)
 130         self.path_order = []
 131         self.pyenv_finder = None
 132         self.asdf_finder = None
 133         self.paths = defaultdict(PathEntry)
 134         self.__finders = {}

 154     @cached_property
 155     def executables(self):
 156         # type: () -> List[PathEntry]
 157         self.executables = [
 158             p
 159             for p in chain(*(child.children.values() for child in self.paths.values()))
 160             if p.is_executable
 161         ]
 162         return self.executables
 163 
 164     @cached_property
 165     def python_executables(self):
 166         # type: () -> Dict[str, PathEntry]
 167         python_executables = {}
 168         for child in self.paths.values():
 169             if child.pythons:
 170                 python_executables.update(dict(child.pythons))
 171         for finder_name, finder in self.__finders.items():
 172             if finder.pythons:
 173                 python_executables.update(dict(finder.pythons))
 174         self._python_executables = python_executables
 175         return self._python_executables
 176 
 177     @cached_property
 178     def version_dict(self):
 179         # type: () -> DefaultDict[Tuple, List[PathEntry]]
 180         self._version_dict = defaultdict(
 181             list
 182         )  # type: DefaultDict[Tuple, List[PathEntry]]
 183         for finder_name, finder in self.__finders.items():
 184             for version, entry in finder.versions.items():
 185                 if finder_name == "windows":
 186                     if entry not in self._version_dict[version]:
 187                         self._version_dict[version].append(entry)
 188                     continue
 189                 if entry not in self._version_dict[version] and entry.is_python:
 190                     self._version_dict[version].append(entry)
 191         for p, entry in self.python_executables.items():
 192             version = entry.as_python  # type: PythonVersion
 193             if not version:
 194                 continue
 195             if not isinstance(version, tuple):
 196                 version = version.version_tuple
 197             if version and entry not in self._version_dict[version]:
 198                 self._version_dict[version].append(entry)
 199         return self._version_dict

 201     def _run_setup(self):
 202         # type: () -> "SystemPath"
 203         if not self.__class__ == SystemPath:
 204             return self
 205         new_instance = self
 206         path_order = new_instance.path_order[:]
 207         path_entries = self.paths.copy()
 208         if self.global_search and "PATH" in os.environ:
 209             path_order = path_order + os.environ["PATH"].split(os.pathsep)
 210         path_order = list(dedup(path_order))
 211         path_instances = [
 212             ensure_path(p.strip('"'))
 213             for p in path_order
 214             if not any(
 215                 is_in_path(normalize_path(str(p)), normalize_path(shim))
 216                 for shim in SHIM_PATHS
 217             )
 218         ]
 219         path_entries.update(
 220             {
 221                 p.as_posix(): PathEntry.create(
 222                     path=p.absolute(), is_root=True, only_python=self.only_python
 223                 )
 224                 for p in path_instances
 225             }
 226         )
 227         new_instance = attr.evolve(
 228             new_instance,
 229             path_order=[p.as_posix() for p in path_instances],
 230             paths=path_entries,
 231         )
 232         if os.name == "nt" and "windows" not in self.finders:
 233             new_instance = new_instance._setup_windows()
 234         #: slice in pyenv
 235         if self.check_for_pyenv() and "pyenv" not in self.finders:
 236             new_instance = new_instance._setup_pyenv()
 237         #: slice in asdf
 238         if self.check_for_asdf() and "asdf" not in self.finders:
 239             new_instance = new_instance._setup_asdf()
 240         venv = os.environ.get("VIRTUAL_ENV")
 241         if os.name == "nt":
 242             bin_dir = "Scripts"
 243         else:
 244             bin_dir = "bin"
 245         if venv and (new_instance.system or new_instance.global_search):
 246             p = ensure_path(venv)
 247             path_order = [(p / bin_dir).as_posix()] + new_instance.path_order
 248             new_instance = attr.evolve(new_instance, path_order=path_order)
 249             paths = new_instance.paths.copy()
 250             paths[p] = new_instance.get_path(p.joinpath(bin_dir))
 251             new_instance = attr.evolve(new_instance, paths=paths)
 252         if new_instance.system:
 253             syspath = Path(sys.executable)
 254             syspath_bin = syspath.parent
 255             if syspath_bin.name != bin_dir and syspath_bin.joinpath(bin_dir).exists():
 256                 syspath_bin = syspath_bin / bin_dir
 257             path_order = [syspath_bin.as_posix()] + new_instance.path_order
 258             paths = new_instance.paths.copy()
 259             paths[syspath_bin] = PathEntry.create(
 260                 path=syspath_bin, is_root=True, only_python=False
 261             )
 262             new_instance = attr.evolve(new_instance, path_order=path_order, paths=paths)
 263         return new_instance
 264 
 265     def _get_last_instance(self, path):
 266         # type: (str) -> int
 267         reversed_paths = reversed(self.path_order)
 268         paths = [normalize_path(p) for p in reversed_paths]
 269         normalized_target = normalize_path(path)
 270         last_instance = next(iter(p for p in paths if normalized_target in p), None)
 271         if last_instance is None:
 272             raise ValueError("No instance found on path for target: {0!s}".format(path))
 273         path_index = self.path_order.index(last_instance)
 274         return path_index
 275 
 276     def _slice_in_paths(self, start_idx, paths):
 277         # type: (int, List[Path]) -> "SystemPath"
 278         before_path = []  # type: List[str]
 279         after_path = []  # type: List[str]
 280         if start_idx == 0:
 281             after_path = self.path_order[:]
 282         elif start_idx == -1:
 283             before_path = self.path_order[:]
 284         else:
 285             before_path = self.path_order[: start_idx + 1]
 286             after_path = self.path_order[start_idx + 2 :]
 287         path_order = before_path + [p.as_posix() for p in paths] + after_path
 288         if path_order == self.path_order:
 289             return self
 290         return attr.evolve(self, path_order=path_order)
 291 
 292     def _remove_path(self, path):
 293         # type: (str) -> "SystemPath"
 294         path_copy = [p for p in reversed(self.path_order[:])]
 295         new_order = []
 296         target = normalize_path(path)
 297         path_map = {normalize_path(pth): pth for pth in self.paths.keys()}
 298         new_paths = self.paths.copy()
 299         if target in path_map:
 300             del new_paths[path_map[target]]
 301         for current_path in path_copy:
 302             normalized = normalize_path(current_path)
 303             if normalized != target:
 304                 new_order.append(normalized)
 305         new_order = [p for p in reversed(new_order)]
 306         return attr.evolve(self, path_order=new_order, paths=new_paths)
 307 
 308     def _setup_asdf(self):
 309         # type: () -> "SystemPath"
 310         if "asdf" in self.finders and self.asdf_finder is not None:
 311             return self
 312         from .python import PythonFinder
 313 
 314         os_path = os.environ["PATH"].split(os.pathsep)
 315         asdf_finder = PythonFinder.create(
 316             root=ASDF_DATA_DIR,
 317             ignore_unsupported=True,
 318             sort_function=parse_asdf_version_order,
 319             version_glob_path="installs/python/*",
 320         )
 321         asdf_index = None
 322         try:
 323             asdf_index = self._get_last_instance(ASDF_DATA_DIR)
 324         except ValueError:
 325             asdf_index = 0 if is_in_path(next(iter(os_path), ""), ASDF_DATA_DIR) else -1
 326         if asdf_index is None:
 327             # we are in a virtualenv without global pyenv on the path, so we should
 328             # not write pyenv to the path here
 329             return self
 330         # * These are the root paths for the finder
 331         _ = [p for p in asdf_finder.roots]
 332         new_instance = self._slice_in_paths(asdf_index, [asdf_finder.root])
 333         paths = self.paths.copy()
 334         paths[asdf_finder.root] = asdf_finder
 335         paths.update(asdf_finder.roots)
 336         return (
 337             attr.evolve(new_instance, paths=paths, asdf_finder=asdf_finder)
 338             ._remove_path(normalize_path(os.path.join(ASDF_DATA_DIR, "shims")))
 339             ._register_finder("asdf", asdf_finder)
 340         )
 341 
 342     def reload_finder(self, finder_name):
 343         # type: (str) -> "SystemPath"
 344         if finder_name is None:
 345             raise TypeError("Must pass a string as the name of the target finder")
 346         finder_attr = "{0}_finder".format(finder_name)
 347         setup_attr = "_setup_{0}".format(finder_name)
 348         try:
 349             current_finder = getattr(self, finder_attr)  # type: Any
 350         except AttributeError:
 351             raise ValueError("Must pass a valid finder to reload.")
 352         try:
 353             setup_fn = getattr(self, setup_attr)
 354         except AttributeError:
 355             raise ValueError("Finder has no valid setup function: %s" % finder_name)
 356         if current_finder is None:
 357             # TODO: This is called 'reload', should we load a new finder for the first
 358             # time here? lets just skip that for now to avoid unallowed finders
 359             pass
 360         if (finder_name == "pyenv" and not PYENV_INSTALLED) or (
 361             finder_name == "asdf" and not ASDF_INSTALLED
 362         ):
 363             # Don't allow loading of finders that aren't explicitly 'installed' as it were
 364             return self
 365         setattr(self, finder_attr, None)
 366         if finder_name in self.__finders:
 367             del self.__finders[finder_name]
 368         return setup_fn()
 369 
 370     def _setup_pyenv(self):
 371         # type: () -> "SystemPath"
 372         if "pyenv" in self.finders and self.pyenv_finder is not None:
 373             return self
 374         from .python import PythonFinder
 375 
 376         os_path = os.environ["PATH"].split(os.pathsep)
 377 
 378         pyenv_finder = PythonFinder.create(
 379             root=PYENV_ROOT,
 380             sort_function=parse_pyenv_version_order,
 381             version_glob_path="versions/*",
 382             ignore_unsupported=self.ignore_unsupported,
 383         )
 384         pyenv_index = None
 385         try:
 386             pyenv_index = self._get_last_instance(PYENV_ROOT)
 387         except ValueError:
 388             pyenv_index = 0 if is_in_path(next(iter(os_path), ""), PYENV_ROOT) else -1
 389         if pyenv_index is None:
 390             # we are in a virtualenv without global pyenv on the path, so we should
 391             # not write pyenv to the path here
 392             return self
 393         # * These are the root paths for the finder
 394         _ = [p for p in pyenv_finder.roots]
 395         new_instance = self._slice_in_paths(pyenv_index, [pyenv_finder.root])
 396         paths = new_instance.paths.copy()
 397         paths[pyenv_finder.root] = pyenv_finder
 398         paths.update(pyenv_finder.roots)
 399         return (
 400             attr.evolve(new_instance, paths=paths, pyenv_finder=pyenv_finder)
 401             ._remove_path(os.path.join(PYENV_ROOT, "shims"))
 402             ._register_finder("pyenv", pyenv_finder)
 403         )

 405     def _setup_windows(self):
 406         # type: () -> "SystemPath"
 407         if "windows" in self.finders and self.windows_finder is not None:
 408             return self
 409         from .windows import WindowsFinder
 410 
 411         windows_finder = WindowsFinder.create()
 412         root_paths = (p for p in windows_finder.paths if p.is_root)
 413         path_addition = [p.path.as_posix() for p in root_paths]
 414         new_path_order = self.path_order[:] + path_addition
 415         new_paths = self.paths.copy()
 416         new_paths.update({p.path: p for p in root_paths})
 417         return attr.evolve(
 418             self,
 419             windows_finder=windows_finder,
 420             path_order=new_path_order,
 421             paths=new_paths,
 422         )._register_finder("windows", windows_finder)

 424     def get_path(self, path):
 425         # type: (Union[str, Path]) -> PathType
 426         if path is None:
 427             raise TypeError("A path must be provided in order to generate a path entry.")
 428         path = ensure_path(path)
 429         _path = self.paths.get(path)
 430         if not _path:
 431             _path = self.paths.get(path.as_posix())
 432         if not _path and path.as_posix() in self.path_order:
 433             _path = PathEntry.create(
 434                 path=path.absolute(), is_root=True, only_python=self.only_python
 435             )
 436             self.paths[path.as_posix()] = _path
 437         if not _path:
 438             raise ValueError("Path not found or generated: {0!r}".format(path))
 439         return _path
 440 
 441     def _get_paths(self):
 442         # type: () -> Generator[Union[PathType, WindowsFinder], None, None]
 443         for path in self.path_order:
 444             try:
 445                 entry = self.get_path(path)
 446             except ValueError:
 447                 continue
 448             else:
 449                 yield entry
 450 
 451     @cached_property
 452     def path_entries(self):
 453         # type: () -> List[Union[PathType, WindowsFinder]]
 454         paths = list(self._get_paths())
 455         return paths

 457     def find_all(self, executable):
 458         # type: (str) -> List[Union[PathEntry, FinderType]]
 459         """
 460         Search the path for an executable. Return all copies.
 461 
 462         :param executable: Name of the executable
 463         :type executable: str
 464         :returns: List[PathEntry]
 465         """
 466 
 467         sub_which = operator.methodcaller("which", executable)
 468         filtered = (sub_which(self.get_path(k)) for k in self.path_order)
 469         return list(filtered)
 470 
 471     def which(self, executable):
 472         # type: (str) -> Union[PathEntry, None]
 473         """
 474         Search for an executable on the path.
 475 
 476         :param executable: Name of the executable to be located.
 477         :type executable: str
 478         :returns: :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` object.
 479         """
 480 
 481         sub_which = operator.methodcaller("which", executable)
 482         filtered = (sub_which(self.get_path(k)) for k in self.path_order)
 483         return next(iter(f for f in filtered if f is not None), None)
 484 
 485     def _filter_paths(self, finder):
 486         # type: (Callable) -> Iterator
 487         for path in self._get_paths():
 488             if path is None:
 489                 continue
 490             python_versions = finder(path)
 491             if python_versions is not None:
 492                 for python in python_versions:
 493                     if python is not None:
 494                         yield python
 495 
 496     def _get_all_pythons(self, finder):
 497         # type: (Callable) -> Iterator
 498         for python in self._filter_paths(finder):
 499             if python is not None and python.is_python:
 500                 yield python
 501 
 502     def get_pythons(self, finder):
 503         # type: (Callable) -> Iterator
 504         sort_key = operator.attrgetter("as_python.version_sort")
 505         pythons = [entry for entry in self._get_all_pythons(finder)]
 506         for python in sorted(pythons, key=sort_key, reverse=True):
 507             if python is not None:
 508                 yield python
 509 
 510     def find_all_python_versions(
 511         self,
 512         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 513         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 514         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
 515         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 516         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 517         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 518         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 519     ):
 520         # type (...) -> List[PathEntry]
 521         """Search for a specific python version on the path. Return all copies
 522 
 523         :param major: Major python version to search for.
 524         :type major: int
 525         :param int minor: Minor python version to search for, defaults to None
 526         :param int patch: Patch python version to search for, defaults to None
 527         :param bool pre: Search for prereleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 528         :param bool dev: Search for devreleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 529         :param str arch: Architecture to include, e.g. '64bit', defaults to None
 530         :param str name: The name of a python version, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 531         :return: A list of :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instances matching the version requested.
 532         :rtype: List[:class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry`]
 533         """
 534 
 535         sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 536             "find_all_python_versions", major, minor, patch, pre, dev, arch, name
 537         )
 538         alternate_sub_finder = None
 539         if major and not (minor or patch or pre or dev or arch or name):
 540             alternate_sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 541                 "find_all_python_versions", None, None, None, None, None, None, major
 542             )
 543         if os.name == "nt" and self.windows_finder:
 544             windows_finder_version = sub_finder(self.windows_finder)
 545             if windows_finder_version:
 546                 return windows_finder_version
 547         values = list(self.get_pythons(sub_finder))
 548         if not values and alternate_sub_finder is not None:
 549             values = list(self.get_pythons(alternate_sub_finder))
 550         return values
 551 
 552     def find_python_version(
 553         self,
 554         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 555         minor=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 556         patch=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
 557         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 558         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
 559         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 560         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
 561         sort_by_path=False,  # type: bool
 562     ):
 563         # type: (...) -> PathEntry
 564         """Search for a specific python version on the path.
 565 
 566         :param major: Major python version to search for.
 567         :type major: int
 568         :param int minor: Minor python version to search for, defaults to None
 569         :param int patch: Patch python version to search for, defaults to None
 570         :param bool pre: Search for prereleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 571         :param bool dev: Search for devreleases (default None) - prioritize releases if None
 572         :param str arch: Architecture to include, e.g. '64bit', defaults to None
 573         :param str name: The name of a python version, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 574         :param bool sort_by_path: Whether to sort by path -- default sort is by version(default: False)
 575         :return: A :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instance matching the version requested.
 576         :rtype: :class:`~pythonfinder.models.PathEntry`
 577         """
 578 
 579         major, minor, patch, name = split_version_and_name(major, minor, patch, name)
 580         sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 581             "find_python_version", major, minor, patch, pre, dev, arch, name
 582         )
 583         alternate_sub_finder = None
 584         if name and not (minor or patch or pre or dev or arch or major):
 585             alternate_sub_finder = operator.methodcaller(
 586                 "find_all_python_versions", None, None, None, None, None, None, name
 587             )
 588         if major and minor and patch:
 589             _tuple_pre = pre if pre is not None else False
 590             _tuple_dev = dev if dev is not None else False
 591             version_tuple = (major, minor, patch, _tuple_pre, _tuple_dev)
 592             version_tuple_pre = (major, minor, patch, True, False)
 593         if os.name == "nt" and self.windows_finder:
 594             windows_finder_version = sub_finder(self.windows_finder)
 595             if windows_finder_version:
 596                 return windows_finder_version
 597         if sort_by_path:
 598             paths = [self.get_path(k) for k in self.path_order]
 599             for path in paths:
 600                 found_version = sub_finder(path)
 601                 if found_version:
 602                     return found_version
 603             if alternate_sub_finder:
 604                 for path in paths:
 605                     found_version = alternate_sub_finder(path)
 606                     if found_version:
 607                         return found_version
 608 
 609         ver = next(iter(self.get_pythons(sub_finder)), None)
 610         if not ver and alternate_sub_finder is not None:
 611             ver = next(iter(self.get_pythons(alternate_sub_finder)), None)
 612         if ver:
 613             if ver.as_python.version_tuple[:5] in self.python_version_dict:
 614                 self.python_version_dict[ver.as_python.version_tuple[:5]].append(ver)
 615             else:
 616                 self.python_version_dict[ver.as_python.version_tuple[:5]] = [ver]
 617         return ver
 618 
 619     @classmethod
 620     def create(
 621         cls,
 622         path=None,  # type: str
 623         system=False,  # type: bool
 624         only_python=False,  # type: bool
 625         global_search=True,  # type: bool
 626         ignore_unsupported=True,  # type: bool
 627     ):
 628         # type: (...) -> SystemPath
 629         """Create a new :class:`pythonfinder.models.SystemPath` instance.
 630 
 631         :param path: Search path to prepend when searching, defaults to None
 632         :param path: str, optional
 633         :param bool system: Whether to use the running python by default instead of searching, defaults to False
 634         :param bool only_python: Whether to search only for python executables, defaults to False
 635         :param bool ignore_unsupported: Whether to ignore unsupported python versions, if False, an error is raised, defaults to True
 636         :return: A new :class:`pythonfinder.models.SystemPath` instance.
 637         :rtype: :class:`pythonfinder.models.SystemPath`
 638         """
 639 
 640         path_entries = defaultdict(
 641             PathEntry
 642         )  # type: DefaultDict[str, Union[PythonFinder, PathEntry]]
 643         paths = []  # type: List[str]
 644         if ignore_unsupported:
 645             os.environ["PYTHONFINDER_IGNORE_UNSUPPORTED"] = fs_str("1")
 646         if global_search:
 647             if "PATH" in os.environ:
 648                 paths = os.environ["PATH"].split(os.pathsep)
 649         path_order = []  # type: List[str]
 650         if path:
 651             path_order = [path]
 652             path_instance = ensure_path(path)
 653             path_entries.update(
 654                 {
 655                     path_instance.as_posix(): PathEntry.create(
 656                         path=path_instance.absolute(),
 657                         is_root=True,
 658                         only_python=only_python,
 659                     )
 660                 }
 661             )
 662             paths = [path] + paths
 663         paths = [p for p in paths if not any(is_in_path(p, shim) for shim in SHIM_PATHS)]
 664         _path_objects = [ensure_path(p.strip('"')) for p in paths]
 665         paths = [p.as_posix() for p in _path_objects]
 666         path_entries.update(
 667             {
 668                 p.as_posix(): PathEntry.create(
 669                     path=p.absolute(), is_root=True, only_python=only_python
 670                 )
 671                 for p in _path_objects
 672             }
 673         )
 674         instance = cls(
 675             paths=path_entries,
 676             path_order=path_order,
 677             only_python=only_python,
 678             system=system,
 679             global_search=global_search,
 680             ignore_unsupported=ignore_unsupported,
 681         )
 682         instance = instance._run_setup()
 683         return instance

 711     def _filter_children(self):
 712         # type: () -> Iterator[Path]
 713         if self.only_python:
 714             children = filter_pythons(self.path)
 715         else:
 716             children = self.path.iterdir()
 717         return children
 718 
 719     def _gen_children(self):
 720         # type: () -> Iterator
 721         shim_paths = get_shim_paths()
 722         pass_name = self.name != self.path.name
 723         pass_args = {"is_root": False, "only_python": self.only_python}
 724         if pass_name:
 725             if self.name is not None and isinstance(self.name, six.string_types):
 726                 pass_args["name"] = self.name  # type: ignore
 727             elif self.path is not None and isinstance(self.path.name, six.string_types):
 728                 pass_args["name"] = self.path.name  # type: ignore
 729 
 730         if not self.is_dir:
 731             yield (self.path.as_posix(), self)
 732         elif self.is_root:
 733             for child in self._filter_children():
 734                 if any(is_in_path(str(child), shim) for shim in shim_paths):
 735                     continue
 736                 if self.only_python:
 737                     try:
 738                         entry = PathEntry.create(path=child, **pass_args)  # type: ignore
 739                     except (InvalidPythonVersion, ValueError):
 740                         continue
 741                 else:
 742                     entry = PathEntry.create(path=child, **pass_args)  # type: ignore
 743                 yield (child.as_posix(), entry)
 744         return

 746     @property
 747     def children(self):
 748         # type: () -> Dict[str, PathEntry]
 749         children = getattr(self, "_children", {})  # type: Dict[str, PathEntry]
 750         if not children:
 751             for child_key, child_val in self._gen_children():
 752                 children[child_key] = child_val
 753             self.children = children
 754         return self._children

 758         # type: (Dict[str, PathEntry]) -> None
 759         self._children = val

 764         del self._children

 766     @classmethod
 767     def create(cls, path, is_root=False, only_python=False, pythons=None, name=None):
 768         # type: (Union[str, Path], bool, bool, Dict[str, PythonVersion], Optional[str]) -> PathEntry
 769         """Helper method for creating new :class:`pythonfinder.models.PathEntry` instances.
 770 
 771         :param str path: Path to the specified location.
 772         :param bool is_root: Whether this is a root from the environment PATH variable, defaults to False
 773         :param bool only_python: Whether to search only for python executables, defaults to False
 774         :param dict pythons: A dictionary of existing python objects (usually from a finder), defaults to None
 775         :param str name: Name of the python version, e.g. ``anaconda3-5.3.0``
 776         :return: A new instance of the class.
 777         :rtype: :class:`pythonfinder.models.PathEntry`
 778         """
 779 
 780         target = ensure_path(path)
 781         guessed_name = False
 782         if not name:
 783             guessed_name = True
 784             name = target.name
 785         creation_args = {
 786             "path": target,
 787             "is_root": is_root,
 788             "only_python": only_python,
 789             "name": name,
 790         }
 791         if pythons:
 792             creation_args["pythons"] = pythons
 793         _new = cls(**creation_args)
 794         if pythons and only_python:
 795             children = {}
 796             child_creation_args = {"is_root": False, "only_python": only_python}
 797             if not guessed_name:
 798                 child_creation_args["name"] = _new.name  # type: ignore
 799             for pth, python in pythons.items():
 800                 if any(shim in normalize_path(str(pth)) for shim in SHIM_PATHS):
 801                     continue
 802                 pth = ensure_path(pth)
 803                 children[pth.as_posix()] = PathEntry(  # type: ignore
 804                     py_version=python, path=pth, **child_creation_args
 805                 )
 806             _new._children = children
 807         return _new

 810 @attr.s
 811 class VersionPath(SystemPath):
 812     base = attr.ib(default=None, validator=optional_instance_of(Path))  # type: Path
 813     name = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: str
 814 
 815     @classmethod
 816     def create(cls, path, only_python=True, pythons=None, name=None):
 817         """Accepts a path to a base python version directory.
 818 
 819         Generates the version listings for it"""
 820         from .path import PathEntry
 821 
 822         path = ensure_path(path)
 823         path_entries = defaultdict(PathEntry)
 824         bin_ = "{base}/bin"
 825         if path.as_posix().endswith(Path(bin_).name):
 826             path = path.parent
 827         bin_dir = ensure_path(bin_.format(base=path.as_posix()))
 828         if not name:
 829             name = path.name
 830         current_entry = PathEntry.create(
 831             bin_dir, is_root=True, only_python=True, pythons=pythons, name=name
 832         )
 833         path_entries[bin_dir.as_posix()] = current_entry
 834         return cls(name=name, base=bin_dir, paths=path_entries)
